    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-19T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-19T14:00:00-05:00" n="749"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AG/10–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GWS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gifford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d749fn1">Repeated to Tripoli and Geneva for <persName
                            corresp="#p_CL1">Clark</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-19T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 19, 1951—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1940. In course conversation with <persName corresp="#p_AR1">Allen</persName>
                    today, we took opportunity stress Dept’s and <persName corresp="#p_CL1"
                        >Clark</persName>’s views re desirability early Libyan independence with
                    flexible date. <persName corresp="#p_AR1">Allen</persName> said Blackley’s views
                    not yet recd this point, but he felt in any event previously suggested dates Nov
                    1 and Nov 8 were out of question. Perhaps later on in Nov might be possible.</p>
                <p>Allen confirmed <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> very hesitant re
                    desirability proceeding with early independence if <persName corresp="#p_PA1"
                        >Pelt</persName> cannot be brought into the line. He felt we wld find
                    ourselves in most difficult position in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> if we
                    presented it with <hi rend="italic">fait accompli</hi> in opposition to <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> commissioner. If <persName corresp="#p_PA1"
                        >Pelt</persName> cld be brought into line (and <persName corresp="#p_AR1"
                        >Allen</persName> was not sure how this cld be done) he felt that it wld be
                    different matter and that we cld then proceed with less likelihood heavy censure
                    which he otherwise fears. We took occasion thruout conversation stress views set
                    forth <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 2063<note n="2" xml:id="d749fn2"
                        >Dated October 17, <ref target="#pg_1345">p. 1345</ref>.</note> and <gloss
                        target="#t_Lidel1">Lidel</gloss> 192,<note n="3" xml:id="d749fn3">Telegram
                        319, from Geneva, October 17, <ref target="#pg_1344">p. 1344</ref>.</note>
                    but it is clear that <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> feels decision
                    must ultimately depend on <persName corresp="#p_PA1">Pelt</persName>’s
                    attitude.</p>
                <p>Allen agreed it wld be desirable if Saadawi cld be brought into line so that
                    Libya cld speak with one voice at sixth <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss>,
                    but was extremely doubtful this cld be done on other terms than offering Saadawi
                    Prime Ministership, which UK wld strenuously oppose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
